*To make a Pod*
kubectl run ayush  --image=nginx/httpd -n prod

*To make a deployment*
kubectl create deployment ayush-deploy --image=nginx/httpd -n prod

*To crete a service*
kubectl expose deployment ayush-deploy --port=80 --target-port=80 -n prod

*To see logs*
kubectl logs pod/ayush -n prod

*To see running pods functions/when a pod is stucked on ImagePullBackOff error*
kubectl describe pod/ayush -n prod
kubectl describe ayush -n prod

*To forward the port of the service*
kubectl port-forward ayush-deploy 8080:80 -n prod

*to see clusters*
kind get clusters

*to see kubectl is listening to which cluster*
kubectl config current-context

**to use the specific cluter**
kubectl config use-context clustername

**to set default namespace**
kubectl config set-context --current --namespace nameofns

*to see namespace*
kubectl get ns

**to delete all the things inside a ns**
kubectl delete all -all -n nsname

*to enter inside pod*
kubectl exec -it pod-name -n prod -- bash

**to set new image**
kubectl set image deployment/name --node=node:20-slim -n node-app

**to check rolling update**
kubectl rollout status deployment/name -n node-app

**to undo the rolling update**
kubectl rollout undo deployment/name -n node-app

kubectl rollout history deployment/name -n node-app

kubectl rollout pause deployment/name -n node-app

kubectl rollout resume deployment/name -n node-app

**to kill all Process of Kubernetes**
killall Kubectl 


